def_cn: (指1990年德统一之前的联邦德国)西德的，西德人的，西德文化的
def_en: West German means belonging or relating to the part of Germany that was known as the Federal Republic of Germany before the two parts of Germany were united in 1990. West German also means belonging or relating to the people or culture of this part of Germany.
A West German is someone who was a citizen of the Federal Republic of Germany, or a person of West German origin.
